83
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,577
Show yourself.

84
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:48,537
Be careful.

85
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:51,954
Even in defeat, saruman is dangerous.

86
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:54,210
Well, let's just have his head
and be done with it

87
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,462
no

88
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:59,131
We need him alive.

89
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:02,673
We need him to talk.

90
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:08,800
Saruman: You have fought many wars
and slain many men, théoden king...

91
00:12:08,978 --> 00:12:10,468
And made peace afterwards.

92
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:15,562
Can we not take counsel together
as we once did, my old friend?

93
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:18,985
Can we not have peace, you and I?

94
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,020
We shall have peace.

95
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:25,074
We shall have peace...

96
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:29,325
When you answer
for the burning of the westfold...

97
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:32,206
And the children that lie dead there!

98
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:37,166
We shall have peace
when the lives of the soldiers

99
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,376
whose bodies were hewn
even as they lay dead...

100
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:43,088
Against the gates of the hornburg,
are avenged!

101
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:50,221
When you hang from a gibbet
for the sport of your own crows...

102
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,394
We shall have peace.

103
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:58,854
(Ggibbets and crows?

104
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,435
Dotard!

105
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:04,739
What do you want, Gandalf greyhame?

106
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:08,234
Let me guess. The key of orthanc.

107
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:11,371
Or perhaps the keys of barad-dur itself...

108
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:15,534
Along with the crowns of the seven kings
and the rods of the five wizards!

109
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:18,624
Your treachery has already cost
many lives.

110
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,206
Thousands more are now at risk.

111
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:23,716
But you could save them, saruman.

112
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:26,218
You were deep in the enemy's counsel.

113
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:29,631
So you have come here for information.

114
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,391
I have some for you.

115
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:40,771
Something festers
in the heart of middle-earth:

116
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:43,231
Something that you have failed to see.

117
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:49,234
But the great eye has seen it.

118
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:53,955
Even now he presses his advantage.

119
00:13:55,752 --> 00:13:59,085
His attack will come soon.

120
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:03,418
You're all going to die.

121
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:09,136
But you know this, don't you, Gandalf?

122
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:13,926
You cannot think that this ranger
will ever sit upon the throne of gondor.

123
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:20,190
This exile, crept from the shadows,
will never be crowned king.

124
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:25,190
Gandalf does not hesitate
to sacrifice those closest to him.

125
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:28,322
Those he professes to love.

126
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:33,949
Tell me, what words of comfort
did you give the halfling...

127
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,489
Before you sent him to his doom?

128
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:44,289
The path that you have set him on
can only lead to death.

129
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:46,795
I've heard enough!

130
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,800
Shoot him.
Stick an arrow in his gob.

131
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:50,966
Gandalf: No.

132
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:53,639
Come down, saruman...

133
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:57,723
- And your life will be spared.
- Save your pity and your mercy.

134
00:14:57,939 --> 00:14:59,224
I have no use for it!

135
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:09,989
Gandalf: Saruman.

136
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:12,991
Your staff is broken.

137
00:15:25,007 --> 00:15:28,499
Grima, you need not follow him.

138
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:32,341
You were not always as you are now.

139
00:15:32,515 --> 00:15:35,348
You were once a man of Rohan.

140
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:36,724
Come down.

141
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:39,601
A man of Rohan?

142
00:15:40,523 --> 00:15:42,764
What is the house of Rohan

143
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:46,602
but a thatched barn
where brigands drink in the reek...

144
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:50,522
And their brats roll on the floor
with the dogs?

145
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:57,495
The victory at helm's deep does not
belong to you, théoden horse-master.

146
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:02,701
You are a lesser son of greater sires.

147
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:06,708
Grima...

148
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,415
Come down.

149
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,216
Be free of him.

150
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:15,380
- Free? He will never be free.
- No.

151
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:18,387
Get down, cur!

152
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:21,393
Saruman!

153
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:24,226
You were deep in the enemy's counsel.

154
00:16:24,734 --> 00:16:26,895
Tell us what you know!

155
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:33,615
You withdraw your guard, and I will tell
you where your doom will be decided.

156
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:36,742
I will not be held prisoner here.

157
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:06,060
Send word to all our allies.

158
00:17:06,234 --> 00:17:09,101
And to every corner of middle-earth
that still stands free

159
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:12,775
the enemy moves against us.
We need to know where he will strike.

160
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:35,881
The filth of saruman_

161
00:17:36,097 --> 00:17:39,885
Is washing away.

162
00:17:40,101 --> 00:17:44,640
Trees will come back to live here.

163
00:17:45,147 --> 00:17:47,308
Young trees.

164
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:49,644
- Wild trees.
- Pippin!

165
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:01,322
Bless my bark!

166
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:03,328
Gandalf: Peregrin took!

167
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:06,161
I'll take that, my lad.

168
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:08,166
Quickly, now.

169
00:18:58,387 --> 00:19:03,927
Theoden: Tonight we remember those who
gave their blood to defend this country.

170
00:19:04,602 --> 00:19:06,638
Hail the victorious dead.

171
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:21,106
No pauses.

172
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:25,449
- No spills.
- And no regurgitation.

173
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,617
So it's a drinking game?

174
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:31,784
Last one standing wins.

175
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,294
Man: What'll we drink to?
Let's drink to victory!

176
00:19:38,469 --> 00:19:39,800
Men: To victory!

177
00:20:23,806 --> 00:20:25,467
Theoden: I am happy for you.

178
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:28,265
He is an honorable man.

179
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:31,135
You are both honorable men.

180
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:38,318
It was not theoden of Rohan
who led our people to victory.

181
00:20:45,202 --> 00:20:48,319
Ah, don't listen to me.

182
00:20:49,165 --> 00:20:50,655
You are young.

183
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,165
And tonight is for you.

184
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,177
Here, here.

185
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:16,556
It's the dwarves that go swimming
with little, hairy women.

186
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:23,187
I feel something.

187
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:27,858
A slight tingle in my fingers.

188
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:30,118
I think it's affecting me.

189
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,747
What did I say?

190
00:21:33,918 --> 00:21:37,251
He can't hold his liquor.

191
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:45,926
(Same over.

