He can do it again.

227
00:24:03,192 --> 00:24:05,854
It's ours!

228
00:24:06,028 --> 00:24:08,690
Ours!

229
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:12,694
We must get the precious.
We must get it back.

230
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:16,235
Patience! Patience, my love.

231
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:20,782
First we must lead them to her.

232
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:26,704
We lead them to the winding stair.

233
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:29,544
Yes, the stairs. And then?

234
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:32,710
Up, up, up, up,
up the stairs we go...

235
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:39,259
Until we come to the tunnel.

236
00:24:39,645 --> 00:24:42,762
And when they go in...

237
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:45,727
There's no coming out.

238
00:24:46,652 --> 00:24:49,564
She's always hungry.

239
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:54,489
She always needs to feed.

240
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:56,070
She must eat.

241
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:58,406
All she gets is filthy orcses.

242
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:01,287
And they doesn't taste very nice,
does they, precious?

243
00:25:01,917 --> 00:25:03,578
No

244
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:08,416
Not very nice at all, my love.

245
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:11,423
She hungers for sweeter meats.

246
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,424
Hobbit meat.

247
00:25:13,595 --> 00:25:18,430
And when she throws away the bones
and the empty clothes...

248
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:21,637
Then we will find it.

249
00:25:21,812 --> 00:25:26,146
And take it for me!

250
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:29,308
For us.

251
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:32,812
Yes we meant "for us.”

252
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:36,448
Gollum. Gollum.

253
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:41,112
The precious will be ours...

254
00:25:41,290 --> 00:25:45,784
Once the hobbitses are dead!

255
00:25:46,295 --> 00:25:47,785
You treacherous little toad!

256
00:25:50,466 --> 00:25:52,798
No! No! Master!

257
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:54,583
No, Sam! Leave him alone!

258
00:25:55,471 --> 00:25:58,133
